      "id": "PopularPost217942",
      "post_content": "First turn [Tormented Soul](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tormented Soul). Assuming they don't keep mana open for removal, it at least becomes a 2-for-2 in card advantage terms (unless they left mana open to hit it as you play the Cloak, which on second turn seems unlikely), plus forcing removal on a one-drop. If they don't remove it, they'll be reduced to topdecking distressingly quickly.",
      "posted_by": "LordRandomness",
